There are no distinct markings or patterns visible on the wingtips; instead, the coloration and texture are consistent throughout the wing, with the tips being the darkest part of the wing.

The wingtips do not display any unique or distinctive features such as spots, stripes, or additional colors that would set them apart from other hummingbird species. However, the combination of the dark color, smooth texture, and pointed shape is characteristic of many hummingbird species, particularly those that feed on nectar and require quick, agile flight.

The tail feathers of the hummingbird in the image are dark, with a slightly iridescent sheen, reflecting shades of blue and green. The tips of the tail feathers appear slightly rounded and are darker than the rest of the tail, creating a subtle contrast.
